A member who is subject to Selection A (Additional member contributions) shall:
receive an allowance for all creditable service as follows:
for normal service retirement as provided by § 22-401 of this title;
for early service retirement as provided by § 22-402 of this title;
for ordinary disability retirement as provided by § 29-106 of this article; and
for accidental disability retirement as provided by § 29-110 of this article;
have the allowance adjusted as provided by Title 29, Subtitle 4, Part III of this article; and
make the member contributions at the rate specified by § 22-214(a) of this subtitle.
